Thunder Squama
A powerful Tacet Discord that appears in the Tacet Field of Desorock Highlands and is capable of using the power of the Electro.

<color=#9656d8>[Conducto]</color>
It preserves <color=#b49f50>high RES</color> against <color=#9656d8>Conducto DMG</color>.
The Thunder Squama resembles the fusion of a human and a lizard. It is able to use Wutherons within the Tacet Field for high-speed maneuvers. Initially, it is judged to be the result of the natural evolution of TDs,.
Huanglong: Desorock Highlands
Inferno Rider

Tacet Field found in the west of Forsaken Abundance with high risk and abnormal oscillation of fusion energy. Which cause the failure of first-time investigation, so we still know nothing about its inside details.

<color=#e15226>[Fusion]</color>
It preserves <color=#b49f50>high RES</color> against <color=#e15226>Fusion DMG</color>.

Inferno Rider's location. Incinero Petals inside this Tacet Field provided large amount of fusion energy. They interfere with not only the investigation device but also people's mind, making one to see illusions and hear hallucinations. Please equip with Protection Device before you enter.
Huanglong: Forsaken Abundance
Crownless

A Tacet Discord observed in the Central Plains, there has been only sighting report for this TD, that of which from the Rover. There is no detailed record of its full appearance, and it is judged to be extremely dangerous according to its energy level.

<color=#7e1f57>[Havoc]</color>
It preserves <color=#b49f50>high RES</color> against <color=#7e1f57>Havoc DMG</color>.
A copy of the Threnodian "Crownless". It resembles a white-armored knight in appearance, and when risen in power, it extends its blood-red wings, presumably because it briefly manipulates the structure of Wutherons in its body, instantly increasing its mobility and attack power. Recently, it has also been observed that it can produce a body structure that mimics human "weapons".
Huanglong: Central Plains
